—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/to_xml.mdЩ@3ed6b801afc9ce8e3fa37dfa74c7ddc5c82b9bce226d8cbff2ce881a3e6d4357­title: to xml‘ЁExamplesЪMOutputs an XML string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note attributes: {} content : [{tag: remember attributes: {} content : [{tag: null attributes: null content : Event}]}]} | to xml
<note><remember>Event</remember></note>

```
When formatting xml null and empty record fields can be omitted and strings can be written without a wrapping record.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note content : [{tag: remember content : [Event]}]} | to xml
<note><remember>Event</remember></note>

```
Optionally, formats the text with a custom indentation setting.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note content : [{tag: remember content : [Event]}]} | to xml --indent 3
<note>
   <remember>Event</remember>
</note>

```
Produce less escaping sequences in resulting xml.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note attributes: {a: "'qwe'\\"} content: ["\"'"]} | to xml --partial-escape
<note a="'qwe'\">"'</note>

```
Save space using self-closed tags.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: root content: [[tag]; [a] [b] [c]]} | to xml --self-closed
<root><a/><b/><c/></root>

```
’ђђЪzTitle: title: to xml
Path: Examples
Content:
Outputs an XML string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note attributes: {} content : [{tag: remember attributes: {} content : [{tag: null attributes: null content : Event}]}]} | to xml
<note><remember>Event</remember></note>

```
When formatting xml null and empty record fields can be omitted and strings can be written without a wrapping record.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note content : [{tag: remember content : [Event]}]} | to xml
<note><remember>Event</remember></note>

```
Optionally, formats the text with a custom indentation setting.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note content : [{tag: remember content : [Event]}]} | to xml --indent 3
<note>
   <remember>Event</remember>
</note>

```
Produce less escaping sequences in resulting xml.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: note attributes: {a: "'qwe'\\"} content: ["\"'"]} | to xml --partial-escape
<note a="'qwe'\">"'</note>

```
Save space using self-closed tags.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {tag: root content: [[tag]; [a] [b] [c]]} | to xml --self-closed
<root><a/><b/><c/></root>

```
—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/to_xml.mdЩ@6335231d4d9929837bfb889d361c0bab12b60e6078f57f5ca96b62a5577796d9­title: to xml‘ҐNotesЪ‚Every XML entry is represented via a record with tag, attribute and content fields.

To represent different types of entries different values must be written to this fields:
Tag entry: 
``{tag: <tag name> attributes: {<attr name>: "<string value>" ...} content: [<entries>]}``
Comment entry: 
``{tag: '!' attributes: null content: "<comment string>"}``
Processing instruction (PI): 
``{tag: '?<pi name>' attributes: null content: "<pi content string>"}``
Text: 
``{tag: null attributes: null content: "<text>"}``
. Or as plain 
``<text>``
 instead of record.
Additionally any field which is: empty record, empty list or null, can be omitted.
’ђђЪ¬Title: title: to xml
Path: Notes
Content:
Every XML entry is represented via a record with tag, attribute and content fields.

To represent different types of entries different values must be written to this fields:
Tag entry: 
``{tag: <tag name> attributes: {<attr name>: "<string value>" ...} content: [<entries>]}``
Comment entry: 
``{tag: '!' attributes: null content: "<comment string>"}``
Processing instruction (PI): 
``{tag: '?<pi name>' attributes: null content: "<pi content string>"}``
Text: 
``{tag: null attributes: null content: "<text>"}``
. Or as plain 
``<text>``
 instead of record.
Additionally any field which is: empty record, empty list or null, can be omitted.
